FBIS4-63924 "drsov102_d_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 Regional Affairs Bashkortostan Signs Power-Sharing Treaty With Moscow Bashkortostan Signs Power-Sharing Treaty With Moscow LD2505183794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1652 GMT 25 May 94 LD2505183794 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] [Text] Moscow May 25 TASS -- Bashkortostan became on Wednesday the second republic after its neighbouring Tatarstan to sign a power-sharing treaty with Moscow. The signing ceremony crowned a final round of negotiations between Russian Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin and Bashkir President Murtaza Rakhimov. The package of signed documents includes agreements on economic cooperation, on foreign trade, on sharing powers in defence industries and state property ownership, on crime fighting and environment protection among others. Drafted agreements on budget and banking relations remained unsigned as the parties failed to reach compromise in these fields.
